gomodel:SYNGO_4900  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In Fig. 4A Srgap2 antibody staining shows a punctate pattern which overlaps with presynaptic marker Synapsin1 and excitatory postsynaptic marker Homer1. In Fig. 4B overexpressed Srgap2-mRFP shows colocalization with overexpressed Homer1c-GFP in dendritic spines.\n\nFigure S4 shows Immunoblots of homogenates and synaptic fractions from P15 mouse brains. SRGAP2 is enriched biochemical fractions of the postsynaptic density (PSD) similar to SAP102 (DLG3).. Experimental description: Charrier et al. 2012: rabbit-anti-SRGAP2 C-terminal, antibody [Guerrier et al., 2009]\nGuerrier et al. 2009: rabbit anti-srGAP2 (gift of Gong Ju, Shanghai JiaoTong University; (Yao et al., 2008))\n\nFrom Yao et al. 2008:\nThe antigen peptides were low homologous domains (LHD) of the respective srGAP amino acid sequences, sorted out using the software CLUSTAL W, as shown in Fig. 1.\n\nFigure 1. srGAP2, residues 811-920: TEDGVVERSSPKSEIEVISEPPEEKVTARAGASCPSGGHVADIYLAN\nINKQRKRPESGSIRKTFRSDSHGLSSSLTDSSSPGVGASCRPSSQPIMSQSLPKEGPDKCSIS" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-05" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4900" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

